HEADWORD: Gliadin
<hw>Gli"a*din</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ glue: cf.
F. <ets>gliadine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Vegetable glue or
gelatin; glutin. It is one of the constituents of wheat gluten, and is a
tough, amorphous substance, which resembles animal glue or
gelatin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

